50|$|The {{album was}} treated with great secrecy before its release and was {{delivered}} to reviewers in a reinforced metal box with a timed, electronic <b>padlockto</b> stop them listening to it before its release date. No airplay of the album was allowed and no singles were released until after its release, {{and there were no}} interviews or promotion given by Brel regarding the album. Despite this, the album reached number one in France and earned Brel a gold record for selling 100,000 albums in 1978 and went platinum in 1981. It is estimated that the album sold 1,127,100 copies.|$|E

